      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET DREAMS NZ (3) has come from wider barriers than this to win both starts at this circuit and distance since crossing the Tasman. Did some work before finding the front and digging deep to get home narrowly. A good draw can see her take another step. SHAZADELE (1) recorded another strong performance last week when she battled on bravely after racing parked to finish third. That made it back-to-back placings here, both from wider draws than this. Should get every chance from the inside barrier. MARYVILLE ALFIE (2) came from the back row to miss by just a neck as runner-up when resuming at this venue. Fitter for that and draws well. IBBIN NADIA (5) hasn't been too far off the placegetters of late, all in higher-graded races than this.",
